			<p class="mt-4">
				Allows adding sitting places for citizens using <Link
					classes=""
					href="https://gist.github.com/ronyx69/0353e26a6b6c1c0a8d5c28c1a1e7401c"
					text="this script"
					theme="externallink"
				/>.
			</p>
			<h4 class="text-xl text-hit-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-hit-gray-950 pb-4 mt-8 lg:mt-12" id="m_parkingspaces">m_parkingSpaces</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Allows adding parking places for cars using <Link
					classes=""
					href="https://gist.github.com/ronyx69/89d48923dbd020c2109686487dcc4d9c"
					text="this script"
					theme="externallink"
				/>.
			</p>
			<h2 class="border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 mt-24 pb-8 text-4xl font-medium text-hit-gray-400" id="save">Save</h2>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="filename">Filename</h3>
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6 mt-4">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						The filename input is on the bottom left, this is what the actual file will be called. It's not recommended to use spaces, dots, or special symbols.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/asset/prop/prsave.jpg" target="_blank">
						<ResponsiveImage
							src={images.prsave}
							naturalHeight={664}
							naturalWidth={779}
							srcWidths={[300]}
							alt="Save asset window"
							format="webp"
							sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 248px, (min-width: 1200px) 183px, (min-width: 1000px) 205px, (min-width: 780px) 448px, (min-width: 580px) 276px, calc(100vw - 48px)"
							class="h-auto w-full"
							loading="eager"
						/>
					</a><p class="explanation">Save asset window.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="asset-name">Asset Name</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">The asset name visible ingame, the name people should search for.</p>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="images">Images</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">There are 2 different folders you can open by clicking the folder icons:</p>
			<h4 class="text-xl text-hit-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-hit-gray-950 pb-4 mt-8 lg:mt-12" id="snapshot">Snapshot</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				On the snapshot image, bottom right corner. Use this one to replace the snapshot, you can replace it with a 1x1 px image to save on the asset file size.
				This image will only be visible in the content manager. It will also default as the Steam preview image, but you can change that separately when
				publishing.
			</p>
			<h4 class="text-xl text-hit-gray-400 font-medium border-b border-hit-gray-950 pb-4 mt-8 lg:mt-12" id="thumbnail-tooltip">Thumbnail &amp; Tooltip</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Below thumbnail, on the right side. Use this one to change the thumbnail (109x100) and tooltip (492x147) of your asset.<br /> Once you change the main
				thumbnail, the hover/active states will update automatically.
			</p>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="local-assets-folder">Local Assets Folder</h3>
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6 mt-4">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>Once the asset is saved, the .crp file will appear in the local assets folder:</p><p class="mt-4">
						<span class="path">%LocalAppData%\Colossal Order\Cities_Skylines\Addons\Assets</span>
					</p><p class="mt-4">
						The AppData folder is hidden by default, you can access it by copying and pasting the path into the file explorer, or pressing <span class="key"
							>Windows+R</span
						> and typing in appdata.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/asset/building/local.jpg" target="_blank">
						<ResponsiveImage
							src={images.local}
							naturalHeight={226}
							naturalWidth={595}
							srcWidths={[300, 400, 500]}
							alt="CRP files in the local assets folder"
							format="webp"
							sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 248px, (min-width: 1200px) 183px, (min-width: 1000px) 205px, (min-width: 780px) 448px, (min-width: 580px) 276px, calc(100vw - 48px)"
							class="h-auto w-full"
							loading="eager"
						/>
					</a><p class="explanation">CRP files in the local assets folder.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h2 class="border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 mt-24 pb-8 text-4xl font-medium text-hit-gray-400" id="publish">Publish</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6 mt-4">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>Once you have saved the asset and reloaded the game, you can publish the asset.</p><p class="mt-4">
						Go to the content manager &gt; assets and find your asset, then click share.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/asset/building/share.jpg" target="_blank">
						<ResponsiveImage
							src={images.share}
							naturalHeight={194}
							naturalWidth={684}
							srcWidths={[300, 400, 500, 600]}
							alt="Share button in content manager"
							format="webp"
							sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 248px, (min-width: 1200px) 183px, (min-width: 1000px) 205px, (min-width: 780px) 448px, (min-width: 580px) 276px, calc(100vw - 48px)"
							class="h-auto w-full"
							loading="eager"
						/>
					</a><p class="explanation">Share button in content manager.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="title-and-description">Title and Description</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">You can change these on the Steam Workshop later.</p>
			<h3 class="mt-16 text-2xl text-hit-gray-400 font-semibold border-b border-hit-gray-500 pb-4" id="steam-preview-image-and-content-folder">
				Steam Preview Image and Content Folder
			</h3>
			<div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row gap-6 mt-4">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						There is a folder icon again on the snapshot image, bottom right corner. Here you can change the Steam preview image, which is the thumbnail visible
						on steam. The largest size the image will be visible is 437x437 (on the front page) but it will get upscaled to 512x512 by Steam so that's the size
						you should use.
					</p><p class="mt-4">
						There is also the content folder, which is where the actual asset file is. You can paste multiple .crp files here if you would like to upload a pack
						of assets.
					</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/asset/building/publish.jpg" target="_blank">
						<ResponsiveImage
							src={images.publish}
							naturalHeight={591}
							naturalWidth={721}
							srcWidths={[300, 400, 500, 700]}
							alt="Publish window and content folder"
							format="webp"
							sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 248px, (min-width: 1200px) 183px, (min-width: 1000px) 205px, (min-width: 780px) 448px, (min-width: 580px) 276px, calc(100vw - 48px)"
							class="h-auto w-full"
							loading="eager"
						/>
					</a><p class="explanation">Publish window and content folder.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
