			<p class="mt-4">On the Steam Workshop page for your asset, you can:</p>
			<ul class="mt-4 list-disc list-inside">
				<li class="mt-4">add it to a collection<br /></li>
				<li class="mt-4">add images and videos<br /></li>
				<li class="mt-4">add contributors and links<br /></li>
				<li class="mt-4">add required items and DLC<br /></li>
				<li class="mt-4">change visibility to friends only or private</li>
			</ul>
			<h2 class="border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 mt-24 pb-8 text-4xl font-medium text-hit-gray-400" id="update">Update</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">
				To update your own item, you must subscribe to it first, then it will show up in the content manager. It won't be the same as a local asset, as it will
				show an "update" button.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4">
				When you click update, click the folder icon, and now you can change the Steam preview image and put your new asset in the content folder. If updating a
				pack, remember to put all the assets inside the content folder.
			</p>
			<p class="mt-4">You can also add more assets to make it a bigger pack.</p>
